explanation:
OS_TimeAssembleFromNanoseconds: direct callee of OS_GetLocalTime_Impl. Its implementation must be inspected to ensure it does not call memcmp to compare null-terminated strings (MISRA violation).
OS_DEBUG: used in the error path of OS_GetLocalTime_Impl. If this project-provided logging wrapper performs any string comparisons (e.g. to handle formatting or log filtering) it could use memcmp incorrectly; inspect its implementation.
clock_gettime: called by OS_GetLocalTime_Impl. Although typically a libc/POSIX function, some projects provide their own implementation/stub; include it to ensure it does not use memcmp to compare null-terminated strings.
strerror: used to produce the error message. If the project provides its own strerror (or a wrap), its implementation must be checked for any memcmp use on null-terminated strings.
